The '''gem drop table''' or '''GDT''' is a [[drop table]] that is accessed by monsters of all kinds. The table mainly drops gems and talismans. The [[rare drop table]] also has access to the gem drop table. The gem drop table also has a chance at rolling the Mega-rare drop table.

The Mega-rare drop table contains mostly empty drops, but also the rune spear, dragon spear and shield left half. The [[Legends' Quest]] must be completed to obtain one of the mega-rare drops.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1121078945800249345|date=24 April 2019|archiveurl=https://reldo.runescape.wiki/i/105979|archivedate=28 May 2020|quote=While the gem table will only give a chance of jumping to that special table (containing the three items you name) if you have done Legends' Quest, other monsters can jump to that table without any quest checks being performed.}} Wearing a [[ring of wealth]] will remove all empty slots from the table.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1089208722918989824|date=26 January 2019|archiveurl=https://reldo.runescape.wiki/i/101038|archivedate=28 May 2020|quote=On the gem table, it removes the 63 empty slots, turning a 1/128 chance of moving to the megarare list into a 1/65 chance.
On the "megarare" table, it removes the 113 empty slots, turning a 4/128 chance of a dragon shield half into a 4/15 chance.
That's a big improvement.}}

[[Free-to-play]] players have very limited access to the rare drop table; they can only get uncut gems.

